Systems	O
and	O
methods	O
are	O
described	O
for	O
concisely	O
encoding	O
into	O
a	O
lexicon	O
(	O
or	O
dictionary	O
)	O
and	O
decoding	O
from	O
the	O
lexicon	O
regular	O
expressions	O
that	O
can	O
represent	O
certain	O
huge	O
word	O
lists	O
that	O
might	O
otherwise	O
be	O
considered	O
unmanageably	O
large	O
.	O
Sets	O
of	O
words	O
(	O
character	O
sequences	O
or	O
‘	O
strings	O
’	O
)	O
that	O
share	O
certain	O
commonalities	O
such	O
as	O
a	O
set	O
of	O
numbers	O
,	O
which	O
share	O
common	O
digits	O
,	O
may	O
be	O
condensed	O
into	O
digital	O
lexicons	O
by	O
representing	O
the	O
set	O
with	O
a	O
regular	O
expression	O
.	O
The	O
regular	O
expression	O
is	O
a	O
string	O
that	O
includes	O
meta-character	O
,	O
where	O
each	O
meta-character	O
is	O
a	O
place-marker	O
that	O
represents	O
a	O
set	O
of	O
at	O
least	O
two	O
normal	O
characters	O
.	O
When	O
accessing	O
or	O
searching	O
the	O
lexicon	O
,	O
the	O
regular	O
expressions	O
are	O
dynamically	O
expanded	O
,	O
as	O
needed	O
,	O
to	O
the	O
underlying	O
,	O
original	O
word	O
list	O
.	O
The	O
methods	O
disclosed	O
are	O
applicable	O
to	O
many	O
lexicon	O
driven	O
language	O
based	O
systems	O
such	O
as	O
spelling	O
verification	O
systems	O
,	O
handwriting	O
recognition	O
systems	O
,	O
speech	O
recognition	O
systems	O
and	O
the	O
like	O
.	O

