20081231	O

BACKGROUND	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
1	O
.	O
Field	O
of	O
the	O
Invention	O
The	O
present	O
invention	O
relates	O
generally	O
to	O
language	O
recognition	O
and	O
more	O
particularly	O
relates	O
to	O
a	O
system	O
and	O
method	O
for	O
creating	O
and	O
using	O
electronically	O
encoded	O
lexicons	O
that	O
include	O
regular	O
expressions	O
for	O
augmenting	O
the	O
lexicon	O
to	O
cover	O
large	O
sets	O
of	O
entries	O
such	O
as	O
fractions	O
,	O
dates	O
,	O
and	O
real	O
numbers	O
.	O

2	O
.	O
Background	O
of	O
the	O
Invention	O
Many	O
software	O
applications	O
,	O
such	O
as	O
spelling	O
verifiers	O
or	O
handwriting	O
recognizers	O
,	O
employ	O
lexicons	O
(	O
or	O
dictionaries	O
)	O
in	O
order	O
to	O
quickly	O
and	O
efficiently	O
derive	O
valid	O
words	O
or	O
qualifying	O
character	O
sequences	O
for	O
comparative	O
or	O
generative	O
purposes	O
.	O
In	O
spelling	O
verifiers	O
and	O
some	O
recognizers	O
,	O
input	O
data	O
(	O
unqualified	O
character	O
sequences	O
)	O
are	O
compared	O
with	O
accepted	O
lexicon	O
entries	O
and	O
are	O
thereby	O
verified	O
or	O
invalidated	O
.	O
In	O
some	O
recognizers	O
,	O
a	O
handwritten	O
word	O
is	O
transcribed	O
through	O
a	O
process	O
that	O
aligns	O
the	O
features	O
of	O
the	O
handwritten	O
word	O
to	O
the	O
best-fitting	O
lexicon	O
entry	O
.	O
In	O
both	O
cases	O
,	O
no	O
valid	O
result	O
is	O
produced	O
unless	O
it	O
is	O
represented	O
in	O
the	O
lexicon	O
.	O
Spelling	O
verification	O
software	O
invalidates	O
misspellings	O
and	O
the	O
lexicon-restricted	O
handwriting	O
recognizer	O
cannot	O
correctly	O
transcribe	O
(	O
unusual	O
)	O
words	O
not	O
found	O
in	O
the	O
lexicon	O
.	O
For	O
example	O
,	O
since	O
the	O
word	O
‘	O
clads	O
’	O
is	O
not	O
typically	O
found	O
in	O
most	O
lexicons	O
,	O
it	O
would	O
likely	O
be	O
invalidated	O
by	O
spelling	O
verifiers	O
and	O
incorrectly	O
transcribed	O
(	O
perhaps	O
as	O
‘	O
dads	O
’	O
)	O
if	O
written	O
and	O
machine-recognized	O
.	O

Large	O
lexicons	O
are	O
desired	O
to	O
provide	O
complete	O
coverage	O
over	O
the	O
legitimate	O
range	O
of	O
items	O
(	O
words	O
,	O
numbers	O
,	O
abbreviations	O
,	O
codes	O
,	O
mnemonics	O
,	O
etc	O
.	O
)	O
that	O
may	O
be	O
entered	O
.	O
Unfortunately	O
,	O
no	O
general-purpose	O
lexicon	O
can	O
even	O
approach	O
completeness	O
since	O
the	O
inclusion	O
of	O
even	O
a	O
reasonable	O
subset	O
of	O
common	O
fractions	O
,	O
dates	O
,	O
and	O
real	O
numbers	O
,	O
for	O
example	O
,	O
would	O
increase	O
the	O
lexicon	O
size	O
by	O
many	O
orders	O
of	O
magnitude	O
.	O
As	O
a	O
result	O
,	O
the	O
word	O
coverage	O
of	O
the	O
recognizer	O
or	O
spelling	O
verifier	O
suffers	O
from	O
either	O
incompleteness	O
or	O
it	O
must	O
be	O
augmented	O
by	O
additional	O
,	O
external	O
logic	O
that	O
must	O
be	O
integrated	O
with	O
the	O
lexicon	O
.	O
Methods	O
that	O
depend	O
on	O
external	O
logic	O
are	O
generally	O
awkward	O
and	O
incomplete	O
.	O
Rule-based	O
methods	O
can	O
be	O
used	O
for	O
generating	O
or	O
evaluating	O
character	O
sequences	O
,	O
but	O
such	O
methods	O
generally	O
require	O
that	O
software	O
be	O
prepared	O
by	O
or	O
with	O
an	O
expert	O
before	O
the	O
lexicon	O
and/or	O
system	O
is	O
released	O
for	O
common	O
use	O
.	O

Such	O
expert	O
or	O
rule-based	O
systems	O
are	O
generally	O
non-extensible	O
,	O
or	O
are	O
only	O
extensible	O
by	O
highly	O
qualified	O
experts	O
.	O
Consequently	O
,	O
a	O
general	O
method	O
for	O
encoding	O
the	O
vast	O
number	O
of	O
more	O
common	O
numbers	O
,	O
fractions	O
,	O
and	O
dates	O
within	O
a	O
lexicon	O
is	O
highly	O
desirable	O
.	O

SUMMARY	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
A	O
method	O
for	O
using	O
regular	O
expressions	O
to	O
represent	O
(	O
typically	O
large	O
)	O
subsets	O
of	O
entries	O
in	O
a	O
lexicon	O
is	O
described	O
.	O
Meta-characters	O
are	O
used	O
to	O
represent	O
a	O
class	O
of	O
characters	O
.	O
One	O
or	O
more	O
meta-characters	O
and	O
(	O
optionally	O
)	O
standard	O
characters	O
are	O
used	O
to	O
create	O
a	O
regular	O
expression	O
string	O
.	O
Each	O
such	O
string	O
represents	O
or	O
encodes	O
a	O
class	O
or	O
set	O
of	O
one	O
or	O
more	O
words	O
or	O
lexicon	O
entries	O
.	O
Regular	O
expression	O
strings	O
are	O
entered	O
into	O
the	O
lexicon	O
with	O
all	O
other	O
lexicon	O
word	O
entries	O
.	O

In	O
accordance	O
with	O
a	O
method	O
for	O
creating	O
an	O
encoded	O
lexicon	O
,	O
a	O
meta-character	O
is	O
defined	O
as	O
representing	O
a	O
set	O
of	O
at	O
least	O
two	O
symbols	O
.	O
An	O
unencoded	O
lexicon	O
is	O
then	O
read	O
and	O
a	O
substitution	O
process	O
is	O
performed	O
where	O
the	O
meta-character	O
is	O
substituted	O
into	O
entries	O
in	O
the	O
lexicon	O
which	O
comply	O
with	O
the	O
meta-character	O
definition	O
.	O
Preferably	O
,	O
the	O
meta-character	O
is	O
a	O
user	O
defined	O
entry	O
in	O
a	O
meta-character	O
definition	O
table	O
having	O
a	O
plurality	O
of	O
meta-characters	O
.	O

A	O
method	O
of	O
searching	O
an	O
encoded	O
lexicon	O
encoded	O
with	O
a	O
meta-character	O
representing	O
at	O
least	O
two	O
symbols	O
includes	O
the	O
steps	O
of	O
submitting	O
a	O
search	O
string	O
having	O
a	O
plurality	O
of	O
symbols	O
;	O
substituting	O
the	O
symbols	O
represented	O
by	O
said	O
meta-character	O
to	O
generate	O
a	O
meta-string	O
;	O
and	O
comparing	O
the	O
entries	O
of	O
the	O
encoded	O
lexicon	O
for	O
at	O
least	O
partial	O
matches	O
to	O
the	O
meta-string	O
.	O
The	O
at	O
least	O
partial	O
matches	O
are	O
then	O
expandable	O
by	O
substituting	O
the	O
meta-characters	O
in	O
the	O
partial	O
matches	O
for	O
the	O
symbols	O
represented	O
by	O
the	O
meta-character	O
.	O

In	O
accordance	O
with	O
the	O
present	O
invention	O
,	O
a	O
method	O
for	O
generating	O
unencoded	O
word	O
hypotheses	O
to	O
test	O
against	O
submitted	O
data	O
uses	O
an	O
encoded	O
lexicon	O
having	O
a	O
tree	O
based	O
structure	O
.	O
The	O
tree	O
based	O
encoded	O
lexicon	O
includes	O
a	O
plurality	O
of	O
entries	O
which	O
have	O
a	O
plurality	O
of	O
linked	O
character	O
nodes	O
,	O
including	O
a	O
first	O
node	O
and	O
a	O
terminal	O
node	O
.	O
At	O
least	O
one	O
of	O
the	O
nodes	O
is	O
a	O
meta-character	O
representing	O
at	O
least	O
two	O
other	O
characters	O
.	O
The	O
generative	O
method	O
includes	O
the	O
steps	O
of	O
generating	O
first	O
hypotheses	O
including	O
first	O
node	O
characters	O
of	O
all	O
entries	O
of	O
the	O
encoded	O
lexicon	O
.	O
The	O
first	O
current	O
hypotheses	O
are	O
tested	O
against	O
the	O
submitted	O
data	O
to	O
determine	O
whether	O
the	O
hypotheses	O
are	O
probable	O
partial	O
matches	O
.	O
For	O
each	O
probable	O
branch	O
identified	O
,	O
those	O
hypotheses	O
are	O
refined	O
by	O
adding	O
characters	O
from	O
subsequent	O
linked	O
character	O
nodes	O
.	O
The	O
refined	O
hypotheses	O
are	O
then	O
tested	O
against	O
the	O
submitted	O
data	O
to	O
determine	O
whether	O
the	O
refined	O
hypotheses	O
are	O
probable	O
partial	O
matches	O
.	O
For	O
each	O
further	O
probable	O
branch	O
which	O
is	O
identified	O
where	O
the	O
current	O
node	O
is	O
not	O
a	O
terminal	O
node	O
,	O
the	O
steps	O
of	O
refining	O
and	O
testing	O
the	O
hypotheses	O
are	O
repeated	O
.	O
For	O
each	O
further	O
probable	O
branch	O
reaching	O
a	O
terminal	O
node	O
where	O
the	O
current	O
refined	O
hypothesis	O
is	O
a	O
probable	O
match	O
to	O
the	O
submitted	O
data	O
,	O
the	O
refined	O
hypothesis	O
is	O
provided	O
as	O
an	O
output	O
indicative	O
of	O
a	O
probable	O
match	O
.	O

In	O
accordance	O
with	O
one	O
form	O
of	O
the	O
present	O
invention	O
,	O
a	O
computer-based	O
language	O
verification	O
system	O
using	O
a	O
lexicon	O
is	O
formed	O
with	O
a	O
first	O
data	O
file	O
having	O
an	O
